notification-daemon: The Desktop Notifications framework
notification-daemon:
notification-daemon: The Desktop Notifications framework provides a standard way of
notification-daemon: doing passive pop-up notifications on the Linux desktop. These
notification-daemon: are designed to notify the user of something without interrupting
notification-daemon: their work with a dialog box that they must close. Passive
notification-daemon: popups can automatically disappear after a short period of time.
notification-daemon: 
notification-daemon: This project consists of a specification
notification-daemon: (http://www.galago.info/specs/notification/index.php) and a
notification-daemon: reference implementation (libnotify and notification-daemon).
